    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-15T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-15T13:00:00-05:00" n="131"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d131">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EAC/206: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-15T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 15, 1944—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5535. Eacom 26, in reply to your Comea 64 of June 20.<note n="99"
                        xml:id="d131fn99">Telegram 4900, Comea 64, June 20, 7 p.m., from London,
                        asked for additional views on the question of stationing token forces within
                        occupied Germany (740.00119 EAC/206).</note> Joint Chiefs of Staff have now
                    expressed their views on participation of other Allied forces in occupation
                    zones of Germany.</p>
                <p>The Joint Chiefs of Staff consider that from a military point of view the
                    provision of token United States forces in enemy areas controlled <pb
                        facs="0264" n="250" xml:id="pg_250"/> by other Allied Nations is
                    inadvisable. However, the Joint Chiefs of Staff consider that there is no
                    objection from a military point of view to the presence in occupied zones of
                    troops of other Allied Nations actually participating in military operations
                    under the authority of the Supreme Commander of the Allied Expeditionary
                    Force.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
